    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Customers say

    Customers find the charging cradle works well with their Bose Portable Home Smart Speaker and appreciate its sound quality, with one customer noting the speaker can face in any direction. Moreover, the cradle is easy to use and customers consider it an excellent base. However, the charging cord and fit receive mixed feedback - while some say it makes charging easy, others note it doesn't come with one, and while many say it fits their speaker perfectly, some mention it doesn't work with the SoundLink Revolve. Additionally, opinions on value for money are divided, with some finding it worth the price while others consider it expensive.

    • Tim Cronin
      5.0 out of 5 stars It should come with the speaker but, it's definitely worth the purchase
      Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2024
      Color: BlackVerified Purchase
      Yes, Bose missed the boat once again by selling the docking station separately but, it's what they do. Kinda like Apple but German. The charging port was taking a beating and felt loose after only a few uses. Having a docking station solves this problem and lengthens the life of a potential charging port failure. Buy it and pretend that it came with the speaker - for $29, you won't regret it.

    • Joe Smart
      5.0 out of 5 stars Should have actually been included with the product
      Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2019
      Color: BlackVerified Purchase
      The Bose Portable Home Speaker can be used both as a portable Bluetooth speaker and as an always-on smart speaker with Amazon Alexa or Google Assistant--but if you do plan to use it as a smart speaker charging it twice a day doesn't really make much sense. Yes, you could just keep it plugged into a wall outlet 24 hours a day but that would make the Bose Portable Home Speaker both a whole lot less portable and also less versatile. With this charging base, you can simply pick up the speaker by its handle whenever you want to use it as a portable Bluetooth speaker in a different room or outside your home and then when done just return the speaker, disconnect your Bluetooth audio device and the Bose Portable Home Speaker automatically turns back into a full-time smart speaker again. The base is so unobtrusive it actually looks like part of the speaker. Since it just needs to rest on the cradle and there are no pins to line up the speaker can face in any direction making the charging cradle extremely easy to use. It's also pretty reasonably priced for an official Bose product accessory but that's probably because it's such a must-have it really should have been included in the package with the speaker in the first place. If you already have the Bose Portable Home Speaker this accessory is a complete no-brainer and the only way to take full-advantage of that expensive speaker.
